n%20%24600%20and%20%24800%20each%20month%2C%20which%20is%20helpful%20%26quot%3Bespecially%20in%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-tariffs-secondhand-clothing-industry-thrift-charity-stores-goodwill-thredup-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eeconomy%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20photographer%20and%20bartender%20Kana%20Kozlowski%2C%2026%2C%20has%20been%20renting%20for%20around%20a%20year.%20She%20earns%20between%20%24200%20and%20%24500%20most%20months%2C%20but%20saw%20a%20bump%20during%20Coachella.%20Across%20the%20platform%2C%20Pickle%20has%20had%20spikes%20in%20rentals%20around%20holidays%20like%20Halloween%2C%20or%20seasonal%20categories%20like%20skiing%20gear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPickle%20also%20helps%20its%20lenders%20price%20their%20rentals%2C%20which%20are%20typically%20listed%20at%2010%25%20to%2020%25%20of%20the%20original%20retail%20price%2C%20McMahon%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2287b5d897-19cb-4bbd-960f-a1d796c123d5%5C%22%3ERentals%20are%20paying%20the%20bills%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20Pickle%20earnings%20go%20toward%20everyday%20expenses%20and%20bills.%20De%20Murguia%20said%20the%20app%20helps%20her%20hit%20savings%20goals%20and%20afford%20social%20outings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20tough%20to%20get%20joy%20from%20being%20a%20full-time%20creative%20when%20you're%20worried%20about%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20Creatore%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20has%20really%20given%20me%20that%20peace%20of%20mind%20again%20to%20fall%20back%20in%20love%20with%20blogging%20and%20photography.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuffield%20recently%20founded%20her%20own%20company%20and%20said%20everything%20she%20makes%20from%20Pickle%20goes%20back%20into%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22112092fa-00ad-44a7-9f48-a25de204fc56%5C%22%3EKeeping%20up%20a%20Pickle%20closet%20takes%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20most%20New%20Yorkers%2C%20De%20Murguia%20has%20a%20lot%20of